1165 12. Pharmacists, intern pharmacists, and registered
1166 pharmacy technicians shall implement and maintain an
1167 electronic log of each transaction. Such log shall include
1168 the following information:
1169 (1) The name, address, and signature of the purchaser;
1170 (2) The amount of the compound, mixture, or
1171 preparation purchased;
1172 (3) The date and time of each purchase; and
1173 (4) The name or initials of the pharmacist, intern
1174 pharmacist, or registered pharmacy technician who dispensed
1175 the compound, mixture, or preparation to the purchaser.
